main event: A witness observed a bright, white, incandescent object that changed to a pale red color, which was likely the planet Venus.
interesting points: The object was described as being similar to a bright star, but ten times as bright.
The object changed color from white incandescent to pale red, and eventually faded to white.
The size of the object was described as being the size of a grapefruit.
The reporting officer concluded that the sighting was undoubtedly caused by the planet Venus.
The duration of the sighting was between 5-10 minutes.
sighted object: a bright, white, incandescent object that changed to a pale red color
